{
  "texts": [
    "The summary graph is represented as 𝐴𝑀𝑅 𝑆𝑢𝑚𝑚𝑎𝑟 𝑦.sentences.",
    "The resulting AMRs are merged into a comprehensive graph representing the entire text, from which key summary segments are then extracted.AMRs are particularly useful for handling complex entity interactions, such as in TV series transcripts.",
    "Summ [42] leverages AMRs to represent individual scenes within an episode.",
    "These scene-level AMRs are subsequently integrated into a hierarchical encoder-decoder model that incorporates a novel cross-level cross-attention mechanism.This approach builds on dialogue-specific AMRs introduced by Bai et al. [5], which enhance traditional AMRs by including speaker nodes, utterance nodes, and improved coreference handling to better capture conversational dynamics.Machine Translation.",
    "Defined as the task of converting source text into a target language, machine translation has also benefited from AMR-based approaches that integrate semantic information from AMR graphs into translation models."
  ]
}